{"key":"processedPost-17834545","value":{"id":17834545,"first":17788866,"last":17854139,"when":1361371797,"utime":"02/20/13 04:49 PM","content":"It's interesting how this type of thread gets repeated every few years.<br />One can use plastic sheeting with pin holes all over it, crinkled up wax paper, crinkled up parchment paper, etc., and grow without even using a fruiting chamber. <br />Bubble wrap fits this genera too, since it holds a micro-climate right at the surface of the substrate.&nbsp; There are lots of materials that could be used including the old standard wax paper, a piece of sheet metal, cardboard, the plastic lids that come with Glad baking trays, etc., etc.<br />The idea is to hold a microclimate right at the surface of the substrate which holds humidity but still allows fresh air to penetrate, which scrubs off the stale air.&nbsp; These are the conditions which are conducive to pinset formation and the number of materials one can use to accomplish the above are limitless.&nbsp; I'm not sure each individual material requires a new 'tek' as they are all doing the same thing; providing a micro-climate at the surface of the substrate. <br />RR","title":"Re: Bubble Wrap VS. Mono Tub + Pin porn (pic heavy)"}}